To terminate a C program, you can use the `exit()` function from the `stdlib.h` library. This function takes an integer argument, which represents the exit status of the program. Here's an example of how to use it:

```c
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    // Your code here

    // Terminating the program
    exit(status);
}
```

In this example, `status` is the exit status of the program. You can set it to 0 for a successful termination or any other value to indicate an error.

